36#define RETERR(x) do { \
37 result = (x); \
38 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) \
39 goto failure; \
40 } while (/*CONSTCOND*/0)
41
42void
43dns_nsec_setbit(unsigned char *array, unsigned int type, unsigned int bit) {
44 unsigned int shift, mask;
45
46 shift = 7 - (type % 8);
47 mask = 1 << shift;
48
49 if (bit != 0)
50 array[type / 8] |= mask;
51 else
52 array[type / 8] &= (~mask & 0xFF);
53}
54
55bool
56dns_nsec_isset(const unsigned char *array, unsigned int type) {
57 unsigned int byte, shift, mask;
58
59 byte = array[type / 8];
60 shift = 7 - (type % 8);
61 mask = 1 << shift;
62
63 return ((byte & mask) != 0);
64}
65
66unsigned int
67dns_nsec_compressbitmap(unsigned char *map, const unsigned char *raw,
68 unsigned int max_type)
69{
70 unsigned char *start = map;
71 unsigned int window;
72 int octet;
73
74 if (raw == NULL)
75 return (0);
76
77 for (window = 0; window < 256; window++) {
78 if (window * 256 > max_type)
79 break;
80 for (octet = 31; octet >= 0; octet--)
81 if (*(raw + octet) != 0)
82 break;
83 if (octet < 0) {
84 raw += 32;
85 continue;
86 }
87 *map++ = window;
88 *map++ = octet + 1;
89 /*
90 * Note: potential overlapping move.
91 */
92 memmove(map, raw, octet + 1);
93 map += octet + 1;
94 raw += 32;
95 }
96 return (unsigned int)(map - start);
97}

99isc_result_t
100dns_nsec_buildrdata(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version,
101 dns_dbnode_t *node, const dns_name_t *target,
102 unsigned char *buffer, dns_rdata_t *rdata)
103{
104 isc_result_t result;
105 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
106 isc_region_t r;
107 unsigned int i;
108
109 unsigned char *nsec_bits, *bm;
110 unsigned int max_type;
111 dns_rdatasetiter_t *rdsiter;
112
113 memset(buffer, 0, DNS_NSEC_BUFFERSIZE);
114 dns_name_toregion(target, &r);
115 memmove(buffer, r.base, r.length);
116 r.base = buffer;
117 /*
118 * Use the end of the space for a raw bitmap leaving enough
119 * space for the window identifiers and length octets.
120 */
121 bm = r.base + r.length + 512;
122 nsec_bits = r.base + r.length;
123 dns_nsec_setbit(bm, dns_rdatatype_rrsig, 1);
124 dns_nsec_setbit(bm, dns_rdatatype_nsec, 1);
125 max_type = dns_rdatatype_nsec;
126 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
127 rdsiter = NULL;
128 result = dns_db_allrdatasets(db, node, version, 0, &rdsiter);
129 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
130 return (result);
131 for (result = dns_rdatasetiter_first(rdsiter);
132 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS;
133 result = dns_rdatasetiter_next(rdsiter))
134 {
135 dns_rdatasetiter_current(rdsiter, &rdataset);
136 if (rdataset.type != dns_rdatatype_nsec &&
137 rdataset.type != dns_rdatatype_nsec3 &&
138 rdataset.type != dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
139 if (rdataset.type > max_type)
140 max_type = rdataset.type;
141 dns_nsec_setbit(bm, rdataset.type, 1);
142 }
143 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
144 }
145
146 /*
147 * At zone cuts, deny the existence of glue in the parent zone.
148 */
149 if (dns_nsec_isset(bm, dns_rdatatype_ns) &&
150 ! dns_nsec_isset(bm, dns_rdatatype_soa)) {
151 for (i = 0; i <= max_type; i++) {
152 if (dns_nsec_isset(bm, i) &&
153 ! dns_rdatatype_iszonecutauth((dns_rdatatype_t)i))
154 dns_nsec_setbit(bm, i, 0);
155 }
156 }
157
158 dns_rdatasetiter_destroy(&rdsiter);
159 if (result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
160 return (result);
161
162 nsec_bits += dns_nsec_compressbitmap(nsec_bits, bm, max_type);
163
164 r.length = (unsigned int)(nsec_bits - r.base);
165 INSIST(r.length <= DNS_NSEC_BUFFERSIZE);
166 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata,
167 dns_db_class(db),
168 dns_rdatatype_nsec,
169 &r);
170
171 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
172}

174isc_result_t
175dns_nsec_build(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version, dns_dbnode_t *node,
176 const dns_name_t *target, dns_ttl_t ttl)
177{
178 isc_result_t result;
179 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
180 unsigned char data[DNS_NSEC_BUFFERSIZE];
181 dns_rdatalist_t rdatalist;
182 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
183
184 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
185 dns_rdata_init(&rdata);
186
187 RETERR(dns_nsec_buildrdata(db, version, node, target, data, &rdata));
188
189 dns_rdatalist_init(&rdatalist);
190 rdatalist.rdclass = dns_db_class(db);
191 rdatalist.type = dns_rdatatype_nsec;
192 rdatalist.ttl = ttl;
193 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rdatalist.rdata, &rdata, link);
194 RETERR(dns_rdatalist_tordataset(&rdatalist, &rdataset));
195 result = dns_db_addrdataset(db, node, version, 0, &rdataset,
196 0, NULL);
197 if (result == DNS_R_UNCHANGED)
198 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
199
200 failure:
201 if (dns_rdataset_isassociated(&rdataset))
202 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
203 return (result);
204}

206bool
207dns_nsec_typepresent(dns_rdata_t *nsec, dns_rdatatype_t type) {
208 dns_rdata_nsec_t nsecstruct;
209 isc_result_t result;
210 bool present;
211 unsigned int i, len, window;
212
213 REQUIRE(nsec != NULL);
214 REQUIRE(nsec->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec);
215
216 /* This should never fail */
217 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(nsec, &nsecstruct, NULL);
218 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
219
220 present = false;
221 for (i = 0; i < nsecstruct.len; i += len) {
222 INSIST(i + 2 <= nsecstruct.len);
223 window = nsecstruct.typebits[i];
224 len = nsecstruct.typebits[i + 1];
225 INSIST(len > 0 && len <= 32);
226 i += 2;
227 INSIST(i + len <= nsecstruct.len);
228 if (window * 256 > type) {
229 break;
230 }
231 if ((window + 1) * 256 <= type) {
232 continue;
233 }
234 if (type < (window * 256) + len * 8) {
235 present =
236 dns_nsec_isset(&nsecstruct.typebits[i], type % 256);
237 }
238 break;
239 }
240 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsecstruct);
241 return (present);
242}

244isc_result_t
245dns_nsec_nseconly(dns_db_t *db, dns_dbversion_t *version,
246 bool *answer)
247{
248 dns_dbnode_t *node = NULL;
249 dns_rdataset_t rdataset;
250 dns_rdata_dnskey_t dnskey;
251 isc_result_t result;
252
253 REQUIRE(answer != NULL);
254
255 dns_rdataset_init(&rdataset);
256
257 result = dns_db_getoriginnode(db, &node);
258 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
259 return (result);
260
261 result = dns_db_findrdataset(db, node, version, dns_rdatatype_dnskey,
262 0, 0, &rdataset, NULL);
263 dns_db_detachnode(db, &node);
264
265 if (result == ISC_R_NOTFOUND)
266 *answer = false;
267 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
268 return (result);
269 for (result = dns_rdataset_first(&rdataset);
270 result == ISC_R_SUCCESS;
271 result = dns_rdataset_next(&rdataset)) {
272 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
273
274 dns_rdataset_current(&rdataset, &rdata);
275 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &dnskey, NULL);
276 RUNTIME_CHECK(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
277
278 if (dnskey.algorithm == DST_ALG_RSAMD5 ||
279 dnskey.algorithm == DST_ALG_RSASHA1)
280 break;
281 }
282 dns_rdataset_disassociate(&rdataset);
283 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
284 *answer = true;
285 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE) {
286 *answer = false;
287 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
288 }
289 return (result);
290}

292/*%
293 * Return ISC_R_SUCCESS if we can determine that the name doesn't exist
294 * or we can determine whether there is data or not at the name.
295 * If the name does not exist return the wildcard name.
296 *
297 * Return ISC_R_IGNORE when the NSEC is not the appropriate one.
298 */
299isc_result_t
300dns_nsec_noexistnodata(dns_rdatatype_t type, const dns_name_t *name,
301 const dns_name_t *nsecname, dns_rdataset_t *nsecset,
302 bool *exists, bool *data,
303 dns_name_t *wild, dns_nseclog_t logit, void *arg)
304{
305 int order;
306 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
307 isc_result_t result;
308 dns_namereln_t relation;
309 unsigned int olabels, nlabels, labels;
310 dns_rdata_nsec_t nsec;
311 bool atparent;
312 bool ns;
313 bool soa;
314
315 REQUIRE(exists != NULL);
316 REQUIRE(data != NULL);
317 REQUIRE(nsecset != NULL &&
318 nsecset->type == dns_rdatatype_nsec);
319
320 result = dns_rdataset_first(nsecset);
321 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
322 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "failure processing NSEC set");
323 return (result);
324 }
325 dns_rdataset_current(nsecset, &rdata);
326
327 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "looking for relevant NSEC");
328 relation = dns_name_fullcompare(name, nsecname, &order, &olabels);
329
330 if (order < 0) {
331 /*
332 * The name is not within the NSEC range.
333 */
334 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
335 "NSEC does not cover name, before NSEC");
336 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
337 }
338
339 if (order == 0) {
340 /*
341 * The names are the same. If we are validating "."
342 * then atparent should not be set as there is no parent.
343 */
344 atparent = (olabels != 1) && dns_rdatatype_atparent(type);
345 ns = dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_ns);
346 soa = dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_soa);
347 if (ns && !soa) {
348 if (!atparent) {
349 /*
350 * This NSEC record is from somewhere higher in
351 * the DNS, and at the parent of a delegation.
352 * It can not be legitimately used here.
353 */
354 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
355 "ignoring parent nsec");
356 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
357 }
358 } else if (atparent && ns && soa) {
359 /*
360 * This NSEC record is from the child.
361 * It can not be legitimately used here.
362 */
363 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
364 "ignoring child nsec");
365 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
366 }
367 if (type == dns_rdatatype_cname || type == dns_rdatatype_nxt ||
368 type == dns_rdatatype_nsec || type == dns_rdatatype_key ||
369 !dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_cname)) {
370 *exists = true;
371 *data = dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, type);
372 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
373 "nsec proves name exists (owner) data=%d",
374 *data);
375 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
376 }
377 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "NSEC proves CNAME exists");
378 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
379 }
380
381 if (relation == dns_namereln_subdomain &&
382 dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_ns) &&
383 !dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_soa))
384 {
385 /*
386 * This NSEC record is from somewhere higher in
387 * the DNS, and at the parent of a delegation or
388 * at a DNAME.
389 * It can not be legitimately used here.
390 */
391 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "ignoring parent nsec");
392 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
393 }
394
395 if (relation == dns_namereln_subdomain &&
396 dns_nsec_typepresent(&rdata, dns_rdatatype_dname))
397 {
398 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
399 "nsec proves covered by dname");
400 *exists = false;
401 return (DNS_R_DNAME);
402 }
403
404 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&rdata, &nsec, NULL);
405 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
406 return (result);
407 relation = dns_name_fullcompare(&nsec.next, name, &order, &nlabels);
408 if (order == 0) {
409 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsec);
410 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
411 "ignoring nsec matches next name");
412 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
413 }
414
415 if (order < 0 && !dns_name_issubdomain(nsecname, &nsec.next)) {
416 /*
417 * The name is not within the NSEC range.
418 */
419 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsec);
420 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
421 "ignoring nsec because name is past end of range");
422 return (ISC_R_IGNORE);
423 }
424
425 if (order > 0 && relation == dns_namereln_subdomain) {
426 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
427 "nsec proves name exist (empty)");
428 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsec);
429 *exists = true;
430 *data = false;
431 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
432 }
433 if (wild != NULL) {
434 dns_name_t common;
435 dns_name_init(&common, NULL);
436 if (olabels > nlabels) {
437 labels = dns_name_countlabels(nsecname);
438 dns_name_getlabelsequence(nsecname, labels - olabels,
439 olabels, &common);
440 } else {
441 labels = dns_name_countlabels(&nsec.next);
442 dns_name_getlabelsequence(&nsec.next, labels - nlabels,
443 nlabels, &common);
444 }
445 result = dns_name_concatenate(dns_wildcardname, &common,
446 wild, NULL);
447 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
448 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsec);
449 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3),
450 "failure generating wildcard name");
451 return (result);
452 }
453 }
454 dns_rdata_freestruct(&nsec);
455 (*logit)(arg, ISC_LOG_DEBUG(3), "nsec range ok");
456 *exists = false;
457 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
458}
